race.comment: Competitive affair to close out the card. Former Victorian TEN DEEP (7) is having her first run for the new stable but should find this easier than what she faced down south. Revved up for this with a recent trial win and should be right there when the whips are cracking. The well-related HEESEN (3) (half to 2xG3 winner California Zimbol) has been thereabouts at the past four efforts and gets 3kg off with the claim. Sure to run well again. CASROCK (10) boasts a win over this course and distance and will be rock-hard fit for this. Top-three prospects. ALLY (9) saves her best form for this six-furlong trip and can feature with any luck in running. BREAK FREE (1) makes some appeal despite the wide draw.
